headline.main: U.S. AID TO FRENCH EXPECTED TO STOP; Weygand Removal Results in Notice of Suspension of All Negotiations on Help

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Nov. 19 -- The ouster of General Maxime Weygand as commander of the French forces in North Africa is expected to lead to the suspension of American aid to that area, at least until its full implications are understood.
